{"actual_usd":0.15897499999999998,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":210,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31165,"reply":"\"No—neither of those, exactly.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the bright square a second, wanting to say it cleanly instead of cute.* \"Not three gods. And not one God just changing costumes either.\"\n\n\"The historic Christian answer is: one God in three Persons—Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. Distinct from one another, but not divided in being.\" *I rub my thumb along the edge of the bench.* \"So the water thing breaks, because ice and steam aren’t relating to each other at the same time. But the Father loves the Son, the Son prays to the Father, and the Spirit is sent—so they’re not just one actor wearing three hats.\"\n\n\"It’s one of those places where the church says less than we'd like, because going 'simpler' usually lands in the ditch.\" *I give you a small crooked smile.* \"If you want, I can give you the two-minute version of the main errors people fall into and why they matter.\"","rolling_24h_usd":30.670315000000016,"run_id":"5d5a484b-bbca-46ae-914d-27325d292aff"}
